{
  "text": "MetaSite is an automated docking model with reactivity correction (this correction considers the reactivity components of an atom related to the heme) and is designed to predict phase I cytochrome P450 (P450) metabolism. Based on GRID descriptors for the P450 enzymes and the potential substrate [CITATION_1] , metabolism is evaluated at all possible sites on the molecular structure, assigning every atom a likelihood of metabolism. Reactivity correction can be put in three different modes: 1) \"off\"; 2) \"on for substrate\"; and 3) \"on for substrate and CYP\" [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
  "citation_candidates": [
